g.text: This IPSO object is dedicated to remote actuation such as ON/OFF
action or dimming. A multi-state output can also be described as a
string. This is useful to send pilot wire orders for instance. It
also provides a resource to reflect the time that the device has been
On/off control. Boolean value where True is On and False is Off.
This resource represents a dimmer setting, which has an Integer value
The time in seconds that the device has been on. Writing a value of 0
A string describing a state for multiple level output such as Pilot
The application type of the sensor or actuator as a string depending
The timestamp of when the measurement was performed.
Fractional part of the timestamp when sub-second precision is used
